reviews.content:
I grew up watching this film. Now that I am older and have an appreciation for culture and history, I can see how this film gave voice to a previously voiceless discontent by an entire segment of the population in the city of Los Angeles. The year after this film gained world-wide attention, Los Angeles was on fire for a week and the national guard patrolled the streets with tanks. Just to be clear - Rodney King was not the reason for the 'L.A. Riots'; the relationship between the L.A.P.D. and the communities in South-Central Los Angeles caused the 'L.A. Riots'. Without this film, I do not believe those riots would have taken place at that time. Most likely, something worse would have happened later - but not in 1992. For better or worse, 'Boyz N The Hood' (1991) created a conversation that permanently changed United States race relations and law enforcement practices.RealReview Posting Scoring Criteria:
